# ── UV Interactives — Environment Variables ───────────────────────────────────
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   For local development: copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values
#   For Vercel production: add these in Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# .env.local is already gitignored — it's safe to put real values there.
# Never commit a file containing real values (no quotes, no spaces around =).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Sanity CMS (required for live content editing) ────────────────────────────
# Your project ID — find it at https://sanity.io/manage
# Looks like: abc12def
VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=

# Dataset name — use "production" unless you created a different one
VITE_SANITY_DATASET=production

# ── Gemini AI (optional — enables Leo's live AI replies) ─────────────────────
# Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# Without this key, Leo still works using the pre-written fact bubbles.
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=
